# Test-First (Red-Green-Refactor)

Every implementation phase follows this cycle:

| Stage | What to do |
|-------|-----------|
| **Red** | Write tests that specify the expected behavior. Run them — they must fail. |
| **Green** | Write the minimal code to make tests pass. Run them — they must pass. |
| **Refactor** | Clean up while keeping tests green. |

Never write implementation code without a failing test first. Tests live in `backend/tests/unit/` mirroring the `src/` structure.
